						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">calima wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The cc65 runtime includes crc32 and adler32. Adler32 is faster.</div><br />I read that Adler32 has some weaknesses in that it's pretty easy to have the same hash value if only a few bytes are changed around.<br /><br />CRC32 in cc65 requires 4 x 256 bytes in RAM. I wouldn't want to use an implementation that needs so many RAM values.</div>

					
