				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I read that Adler32 has some weaknesses in that it's pretty easy to have the same hash value if only a few bytes are changed around.</div><br />That's a <em>cryptographic</em> weakness, i.e. it's easy for an attacker to modify the data without changing the hash. That's a different problem than just detecting errors in transmission.<br /><br />You don't need to worry about attacks, though, users can already modify stuff easily in this case.<br /><br />Your problem is just error detection, which Adler32 is actually designed for and relatively good at.<br /><br /><br />Edit: LOL ninja'd by lidnariq making the exact same distinction i did.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

